    <cas:Sofa xmi:id="1" sofaNum="1" sofaID="_InitialView" mimeType="text" sofaString="A total of 1,057 explosives-related casualties have been recorded in the first 9 months of the year, 77 per cent of whom were children. Of these casualties, 897 were men and boys, whose deaths and injuries place a significant burden on women, who often have to become the head of household, while carrying out their prior duties and tending to their injured family member at the same time. Mine and ERW casualties among women and girls increased five-fold over the last five years. While explosive hazards remain a humanitarian concern right across Afghanistan, the south (Kandahar, Hilmand, Zabul, Uruzgan), south-east (Ghazni, Paktya), and east of the country (Nangarhar, Kunar) are most affected. Other significantly impacted provinces include Faryab (north), Hirat and Farah (both west). These eleven provinces saw 70 per cent of mine and ERW casualties between 2011 and 2018, with the same trend continuing in 2019."/>
    <cas:View sofa="1" members="8 19 24 29 34 39 44 49 62 75 88 101 114 127 140 153 166 179 192 205 218 231 244 257 270 283 296 309 322 335 348 361 374 387 400 413 426 439 452 465 478 491 504 517 530 543 556 569 582 595 608 621 634 647 660 673 686 699 712 725 738 751 764 777 790 803 816 829 842 855 868 881 894 907 920 933 946 959 972 985 998 1011 1024 1037 1050 1063 1076 1089 1102 1115 1128 1141 1154 1167 1180 1193 1206 1219 1232 1245 1258 1271 1284 1297 1310 1323 1336 1349 1362 1375 1388 1401 1414 1427 1440 1453 1466 1479 1492 1505 1518 1531 1544 1557 1570 1583 1596 1609 1622 1635 1648 1661 1674 1687 1700 1713 1726 1739 1752 1765 1778 1791 1804 1817 1830 1843 1856 1869 1882 1895 1908 1921 1934 1947 1960 1973 1986 1999 2012 2025 2038 2051 2064 2077 2090 2103 2116 2129 2142 2155 2168 2181 2194 2207 2220 2233 2246 2259 2272 2285 2298 2311 2324 2337 2350 2363 2368 2380 2392 2397 2409 2414 2426 2431 2484 2450 2455 2460 2465 2496 2511 2501 2506 2373 2443 2530 2385 2537 2402 2419 2436 2489 2470 2477 2516 2523 2544 2551 2547 2554 2558 2571"/>
